\#\# Error Handling & Fallbacks {\#error-handling}

\#\#\# \*\*Error Categories\*\*

\*\*1. Agent 1 Failure\*\*

\- LLM timeout

\- Malformed JSON response

\- Invalid routing decision

\*\*2. Agent 2 Failure\*\*

\- Tool call failures (SQL errors, vector search timeout)

\- Partial retrieval (some tools succeed, others fail)

\- Empty results (no chunks found, no user data)

\*\*3. Agent 3 Failure\*\*

\- LLM timeout

\- Response doesn't follow behavioral principles (rare)

\- Output is cut off mid-sentence

\#\#\# \*\*Fallback Strategies\*\*

\#\#\#\# \*\*Agent 1 Fallback\*\*

\`\`\`

IF Agent 1 fails or returns invalid JSON:

    

    Option 1: Retry with simplified prompt

        \- Strip examples, keep core logic

        \- If still fails, go to Option 2

    

    Option 2: Default to "medium" context package

        \- rag\_search: required, broad, user's stage

        \- user\_data: snapshot

        \- historical: not required

        \- Essentially: "when in doubt, pull reasonable amount of context"

    

    Option 3: (Last resort) Call Agent 3 with session memory only

        \- Log as degraded experience

        \- Agent 3 trained to handle this: "I'd need more context to give you specific guidance..."

\`\`\`

\#\#\#\# \*\*Agent 2 Fallback\*\*

\`\`\`

IF RAG search fails:

    \- Continue with user\_data only

    \- Mark rag\_results as "unavailable"

    \- Agent 3 proceeds with available context

IF user\_data queries fail:

    \- Continue with RAG results only

    \- Mark user\_data as "unavailable"

    \- Agent 3 gives more generic (but still framework-grounded) guidance

IF all tools fail:

    \- Return minimal context package with only user\_stage

    \- Agent 3 gives conceptual/educational response

    \- Log as critical failure for investigation

Principle: Proceed with what you have, be honest about what you don't

\`\`\`

\#\#\#\# \*\*Agent 3 Fallback\*\*

\`\`\`

IF Agent 3 times out:

    \- Retry with lower max\_tokens (1500)

    \- If still fails, return: "I'm having trouble formulating a response right now. Could you rephrase your question?"

IF response is cut off:

    \- Detect incomplete sentence (no closing punctuation)

    \- Append: "...\[response continued in next message\]"

    \- Log for manual review

IF response violates behavioral principles (detected via validation):

    \- Log for training data

    \- Still return to user (don't block response)

    \- Flag for review

\`\`\`

\#\#\# \*\*Graceful Degradation Tiers\*\*

\`\`\`

Tier 1: Full Experience (Target)

\- All 3 agents working

\- Complete context assembly

\- High-quality synthesis

Tier 2: Partial Context (Acceptable)

\- Agent 1 or 2 has partial failure

\- Some context missing but enough to respond

\- Agent 3 acknowledges gaps, provides directional guidance

Tier 3: Session Memory Only (Degraded)

\- Agent 2 fully fails

\- Agent 3 works with conversation history only

\- Useful for follow-ups, limited for new topics

Tier 4: Error Message (Failure)

\- Agent 3 fails or times out

\- User sees: "I'm having trouble right now. Please try again in a moment."

\- All failures logged for investigation

## **Data Schemas {\#data-schemas}**

### **Session Storage**

sql  
\-- Store session metadata  
CREATE TABLE virtual\_cso\_sessions (  
    session\_id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen\_random\_uuid(),  
    user\_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,  
    thinking\_persona TEXT DEFAULT 'strategic',  
    session\_goal TEXT,  
    created\_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),  
    last\_active\_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),  
    status TEXT DEFAULT 'active'  
);

\-- Store individual messages  
CREATE TABLE virtual\_cso\_messages (  
    message\_id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen\_random\_uuid(),  
    session\_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES virtual\_cso\_sessions(session\_id) ON DELETE CASCADE,  
    role TEXT NOT NULL, \-- 'user' or 'assistant'  
    content TEXT NOT NULL,  
    created\_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),  
      
    \-- Metadata for debugging  
    agent\_1\_decision JSONB, \-- Routing decision (if role \= 'assistant')  
    context\_package JSONB, \-- Full context (if role \= 'assistant')  
    tokens\_used INT  
);

\-- Indexes  
CREATE INDEX idx\_sessions\_user\_id ON virtual\_cso\_sessions(user\_id);  
CREATE INDEX idx\_sessions\_last\_active ON virtual\_cso\_sessions(last\_active\_at DESC);  
CREATE INDEX idx\_messages\_session\_id ON virtual\_cso\_messages(session\_id);  
CREATE INDEX idx\_messages\_created\_at ON virtual\_cso\_messages(created\_at);

### **Logging & Debugging**

sql  
\-- Log routing decisions for analysis  
CREATE TABLE virtual\_cso\_routing\_log (  
    log\_id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen\_random\_uuid(),  
    session\_id UUID REFERENCES virtual\_cso\_sessions(session\_id),  
    user\_message TEXT,  
    query\_type TEXT,  
    confidence FLOAT,  
    context\_prescription JSONB,  
    created\_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()  
);

\-- Log retrieval performance  
CREATE TABLE virtual\_cso\_retrieval\_log (  
    log\_id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen\_random\_uuid(),  
    session\_id UUID REFERENCES virtual\_cso\_sessions(session\_id),  
    tool\_name TEXT,  
    success BOOLEAN,  
    latency\_ms INT,  
    error\_message TEXT,  
    created\_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()  
);

\-- Log errors for debugging  
CREATE TABLE virtual\_cso\_errors (  
    error\_id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen\_random\_uuid(),  
    session\_id UUID REFERENCES virtual\_cso\_sessions(session\_id),  
    agent TEXT, \-- 'agent\_1' | 'agent\_2' | 'agent\_3'  
    error\_type TEXT,  
    error\_message TEXT,  
    stack\_trace TEXT,  
    created\_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()  
);  
